Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop a #deep saucepan{} (with a tight-fitting lid) on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.

Once hot, add the garlic and cook for ~{30%secs}. Stir in the @basmati rice{100%g} until coated, ~{1%min}. Add the @water{200%ml} and the @chicken stock paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil, then turn the heat down to medium and cover with the #lid{}.

Leave to cook for ~{10%mins}, then remove the #saucepan{} from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%mins} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, trim the @aubergine{1}, then halve lengthways. Slice widthways into 1cm pieces.

Pop the aubergine onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, sprinkle over half the @chermoula spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast the aubergine on the top shelf until soft and golden, ~{18-20%mins}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, add the @British chicken breasts{2} and remaining chermoula spice mix. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then rub to coat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, lay the chicken into the pan and cook until browned, ~{5%mins} each side.

Once browned, lay the chicken onto a baking tray and roast on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{15-20%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When cooked, remove from your oven, cover with #foil{} and allow to rest for a couple of mins.

While the chicken roasts, roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch} (stalks and all).

Halve the @red chilli{1/2}, deseed, then finely chop (see ingredients for amount).

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g} and half the parsley.

When everything's ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through the @harissa paste{50%g} and remaining parsley. Slice the chicken into 1cm slices.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the roasted aubergine and chicken.

Drizzle over the parsley yoghurt. Sprinkle with the chilli to finish (add less if you'd prefer things milder).

Enjoy!